{"sha": "093b075d327d1c7c7e0730e46f1d5c2d4aa47f5a", "node_id": "C_kwDOAAsO6NoAKDA5M2IwNzVkMzI3ZDFjN2M3ZTA3MzBlNDZmMWQ1YzJkNGFhNDdmNWE", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Martin Nordholts", "email": "enselic@gmail.com", "date": "2022-10-02T15:31:43Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Martin Nordholts", "email": "enselic@gmail.com", "date": "2022-10-02T15:49:36Z"}, "message": "rustc: Use `unix_sigpipe` instead of `rustc_driver::set_sigpipe_handler`\n\nThis is the first (known) step towards starting to use `unix_sigpipe` in\nthe wild. Eventually, `rustc_driver::set_sigpipe_handler` can be removed\nand all clients can use `unix_sigpipe` instead.\n\nFor now we just start using `unix_sigpipe` in once place: `rustc`\nitself.\n\nIt is easy to manually verify this change. If you remove\n`#[unix_sigpipe = \"sig_dfl\"]` and run `./x.py build` you will get an ICE\nwhen you do `./build/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/stage1/bin/rustc --help |\nfalse`. Add back `#[unix_sigpipe = \"sig_dfl\"]` and the ICE disappears\nagain.", "tree": {"sha": "49ae7a0d88fe87c54350fcd33f83de2dba53e570", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/49ae7a0d88fe87c54350fcd33f83de2dba53e570"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/093b075d327d1c7c7e0730e46f1d5c2d4aa47f5a", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/093b075d327d1c7c7e0730e46f1d5c2d4aa47f5a", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/093b075d327d1c7c7e0730e46f1d5c2d4aa47f5a", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/093b075d327d1c7c7e0730e46f1d5c2d4aa47f5a/comments", "author": {"login": "Enselic", "id": 115040, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExNTA0MA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/115040?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Enselic", "html_url": "https://github.com/Enselic", "followers_url": "https://